		<h2>Compass plugin</h2>
		<h3>Install</h3>
		<code><pre>
	gem install compass-scalablegs-plugin
		</pre></code>
		<ul>
			<li>Create a Scalablegs-based Compass Project</li>
		</ul>
		<code><pre>
	compass create -r scalable my_project --using scalable
		</code></pre>
		<ul>
			<li>Or, If you prefer to use Sass's indentation based syntax:</li>
		</ul>
		<code><pre>
	compass create -r scalable my_project --using scalable --syntax sass
		</code></pre>
		<p>Then edit your `scalable.sass` accordingly.</p>
		<h3>Customising your Grid System</h3>
		<p>This plugin uses the following configuration variables:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>$scalable-columns` (default: 20) controls the default number of grid columns<li>
			<li>$scalable-grid-min-width` (default: 26em - with the assumption of a 12px body font size) controls the default minimum site width</li>
			<li>$scalable-grid-max-width` (default: 82em - with the assumption of a 12px body font size) controls the default maximum site width</li>
			<li>$scalable-gutter-width` (default: 2%) controls the default gutter width</li>
		</ul>
		<p>All of the mixins included with this plugin use these configuration variables as defaults if the corresponding argument is omitted from a mixin call.</p>
