<article id="contribute" class="grid_12-12">
	<h1>Contribute</h1>
	<p>Scalable.gs is divided into tree parts for your convenience.</p>
	<h2>1 - The framework</h2>
	<p>You have full insight into how all this works and are you could <a href="https://github.com/KDN/scalable.gs">contribute to further development/refinements of the framework over on github</a>.</p>
	<h2>2 - Custom generator</h2>
	<p>This part of Scalable.gs is an application that generate code based upon the framework idea, in fact it is the application that outputs this website. You can <a href="https://github.com/KDN/scalablegsapp">view and contribute to the source code on Github</a>.</p>
	<h2>3 - Compass plugin for rails</h2>
	<p>The compass plugin generates either SCSS or SASS on request when the gem is installed. <a href="https://github.com/KDN/compass-scalablegs-plugin">Contribute to the compass plugin on Github</a></p>
</article>

